  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For I will give you a mouth,.... A faculty of speaking, a freedom of expression, a door of utterance, a good degree of elocution, to speak properly, pertinently and freely to any point: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and wisdom; to answer with great propriety, and in the most prudent manner, to any difficult and ensnaring question; and to furnish with such knowledge of the Gospel, and with such gifts and abilities to preach and defend it, that they should be able to give a clear and distinct account of it, and prove every point in it, by the most strong and convincing arguments, and vindicate it against all objections: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which all your adversaries shall not be able to gainsay or resist. This was remarkably fulfilled in Peter, and John, and in Stephen, Acts 4:13. The first word, \"gainsay\", is left out in the Syriac and Persic versions. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "which all your adversaries shall not be able to gainsay or resist. This was remarkably fulfilled in Peter, and John, and in Stephen, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 4:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The first word, \"gainsay\", is left out in the Syriac and Persic versions. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
